obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43590)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Bombay Reorganisation Act, 1960.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43590&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43591)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43591&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 1st day of May, 1960;`
  line
  line `(b) "article" means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "assembly constituency", "council constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have the`
  line `same meaning as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(d) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having, immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the`
  line `whole or in any part of the State of Bombay;`
  line
  line `(e) "notified order" means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "population ratio", in relation to the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat, means the ratio of`
  line `66.31 to 33.69;`
  line
  line `(g) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of the State of`
  line `Bombay, means a person who, immediately before the appointed day, is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(h) "transferred territory" means the territories which, as from the appointed day, are the`
  line `territories of the State of Gujarat;`
  line
  line `(i) "treasury" includes a sub-treasury;`
  line
  line `(j) any reference to a district, taluka, village or other territorial division of the State of Bombay`
  line `shall be construed as a reference to the area comprised within that territorial division as recognised`
  line `for land revenue purposes on the 1st day of December, 1959.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43592)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Formation of Gujarat State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43592&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, there shall be formed a new State`
  line `to be known as the State of Gujarat comprising the following territories of the State of Bombay,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Banaskantha, Mehsana, Sabarkantha, Ahmedabad, Kaira, Panch-mahals, Baroda, Broach,`
  line `Surat, Dangs, Amreli, Surendranagar, Rajkot, Jamnagar, Junagadh, Bhavnagar and Kutch districts;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the villages in Umbergaon taluka of Thana district, the villages in Nawapur and Nandurbar`
  line `talukas of West Khandesh district and the villages in Akkalkuwa and Taloda talukas of West`
  line `Khandesh district, respectively specified in Parts I, II and III of the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `and thereupon, the said territories shall cease to form part of the State of Bombay, and the residuary State`
  line `of Bombay shall be known as the State of Maharashtra.`
  line
  line `(2) The villages in Umbergaon taluka specified in Part I of the First Schedule shall form a separate`
  line `taluka of the same name and be included in Surat district, and the remaining villages in the said taluka`
  line `shall be included in, and form part of, Dahanu taluka of Thana district; and the villages specified in`
  line `Parts II and III of the First Schedule shall respectively be included in, and form part of, Songadh taluka of`
  line `Surat district and Sagbara taluka of Broach district.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43593)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of the First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43593&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "1. THE STATES",`
  line
  line `(a) for entry 4, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:`
  line
  line `"4. Gujarat The territories referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3 of the Bombay Reorganisation Act, 1960.";`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 7, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:`
  line
  line `"8. Maharashtra The territories specified in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 8 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956,`
  line `but excluding the territories referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Bombay`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1960."; and`
  line
  line `(c) entries 8 to 14 shall be renumbered as entries 9 to 15 respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43594)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Saving powers of State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43594&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall be`
  line `deemed to affect the power of the State Government to alter, after the appointed day, the name, extent or`
  line `boundaries of any district, taluka or village in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43595)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Amendment of the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43595&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, there`
  line `shall be allotted 19 seats to the State of Maharashtra, and 11 seats to the State of Gujarat, in the Council`
  line `of States, and in the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table,—`
  line
  line `(a) for entry 4, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"4. Gujarat . . 11";`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 7, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"8. Maharashtra . . 19";`
  line
  line `(c) entries 8 to 18 shall be renumbered as entries 9 to 19 respectively; and`
  line
  line `(d) for the figures "221" the figures "224" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43596)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43596&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The twelve sitting members of the Council of States`
  line `representing the State of Bombay, whose names are specified in Part I of the Second Schedule, and such`
  line `six of the nine sitting members elected to represent that State at the biennial elections held for the purpose`
  line `of filling the vacancies existing on the 3rd day of April, 1960, as the Chairman of the Council of States`
  line `shall by order specify shall, as from the appointed day, be deemed to have been duly elected to fill`
  line `eighteen of the nineteen seats allotted to the State of Maharashtra.`
  line
  line `(2) The five sitting members of the Council of States representing the State of Bombay, whose names`
  line `are specified in Part II of the Second Schedule, and the remaining three of the nine members elected at the`
  line `said biennial elections shall, as from the appointed day, be deemed to have been duly elected to fill eight`
  line `of the eleven seats allotted to the State of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43597)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Bye-elections to fill vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43597&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the appointed day, bye-elections shall be`
  line `held to fill the additional seats allotted to the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat as well as the existing`
  line `casual vacancy in the seats allotted to the State of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43598)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43598&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of the sitting members and of the member chosen to fill`
  line `the casual vacancy shall remain unaltered.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the member elected to fill the one additional seat allotted to the State of`
  line `Maharashtra shall expire on the 2nd day of April, 1966.`
  line
  line `(3) Out of the two members elected to fill the two additional seats allotted to the State of Gujarat, the`
  line `term of office of that member who, at the counting of votes, is last declared elected, or if an equality of`
  line `votes is found to exist, the term of office of such one of them as the returning officer shall decide by lot,`
  line `shall expire on the 2nd day of April, 1964 and the term of office of the other member shall expire on the`
  line `2nd day of April, 1966.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43599)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Representation in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43599&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, there shall be allotted`
  line `44 seats to the State of Maharashtra, and 22 seats to the State of Gujarat, in the House of the People, and`
  line `in the First Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950)—`
  line
  line `(a) for entry 4, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"4. Gujarat . . 22";`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 7, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"8. Maharashtra . . 44"; and`
  line
  line `(c) entries 8 to 22 shall be renumbered as entries 9 to 23 respectively`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (43600)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Delimitation of parliamentary constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43600&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the First Schedule`
  line `to the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1956, shall stand amended as`
  line `directed in the Third Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (43601)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43601&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every sitting member of the House of the People representing`
  line `a constituency which, on the appointed day, by virtue of the provisions of section 11, stands allotted, with`
  line `or without alteration of boundaries, to the State of Maharashtra or to the State of Gujarat, shall be deemed`
  line `to have been elected to the House of the People by that constituency as so allotted.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (43602)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Strength of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43602&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the total number of seats`
  line `to be filled by persons chosen by direct election in the Legislative Assemblies of Maharashtra and Gujarat`
  line `shall be 264 and 132 respectively, and in the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People`
  line `Act, 1950 (43 of 1950)—`
  line
  line `(a) for entry 4, the following entry shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"4. Gujarat . . 132";`
  line
  line `(b) after entry 7, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"8. Maharashtra . . 264"; and`
  line
  line `(c) entries 8 to 13 shall be renumbered as entries 9 to 14 respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (43603)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Delimitation of assembly constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43603&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the Second Schedule to`
  line `the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1956, shall stand amended as`
  line `directed in the Fourth Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (43604)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Allocation of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43604&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of Bombay`
  line `representing a constituency which on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 14 stands`
  line `transferred, whether with or without alteration of boundaries, to the State of Gujarat shall, as from that`
  line `day, cease to be a member of the Legislative Assembly of Bombay and shall be deemed to have been`
  line `elected to the Legislative Assembly of Gujarat by that constituency as so transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) All other sitting members of the Legislative Assembly of Bombay shall become members of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Maharashtra and any such sitting member representing a constituency the extent`
  line `or the name and extent of which are altered by virtue of the provisions of section 14 shall be deemed to`
  line `have been elected to the Legislative Assembly of Maharashtra by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(3) The sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of Bombay nominated to that Assembly under`
  line `article 333 to represent the Anglo-Indian community shall be deemed to have been nominated to represent`
  line `the said community in the Legislative Assembly of Maharashtra under that article.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (43605)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Duration of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43605&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The period of five years referred to in clause (1) of`
  line `article 172 of the Constitution shall, in the case of the Legislative Assembly of Maharashtra or Gujarat, be`
  line `deemed to have commenced on the date on which it actually commenced in the case of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Bombay.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (43606)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Speakers and Deputy Speakers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43606&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The persons who immediately before the appointed day`
  line `are the Speaker and Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of Bombay shall be the Speaker and`
  line `Deputy Speaker respectively of the Legislative Assembly of Maharashtra.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Legislative Assembly of Gujarat shall choose two`
  line `members of that Assembly to be respectively Speaker and Deputy Speaker thereof and until they are so`
  line `chosen, the duties of the office of Speaker shall be performed by such member of the Assembly as the`
  line `Governor may appoint for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (43607)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43607&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The rules as to procedure and conduct of business in force immediately`
  line `before the appointed day with respect to the Legislative Assembly of Bombay shall, until rules are made`
  line `under clause (1) of article 208, have effect in relation to the Legislative Assembly of Maharashtra or of`
  line `Gujarat, subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Speaker thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (43608)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Special provisions in relation to Gujarat Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43608&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The total number of seats`
  line `in the Legislative Assembly of Gujarat to be filled by persons chosen by direct election on the expiration`
  line `of the duration of that Assembly under section 16 or on its dissolution shall be increased from 132 to 154;`
  line `and accordingly, as from the date of such expiration or dissolution, in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), in entry 4, for the figures "132", the figures "154"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Election Commission`
  line `shall determine in the manner hereinafter provided—`
  line
  line `(a) the number of seats to be reserved for the scheduled castes and the scheduled tribes of the`
  line `State in the Legislative Assembly, having regard to the relevant provisions of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) the assembly constituencies into which the State shall be divided, the extent of each of such`
  line `constituencies and in which of them seats shall be reserved for the scheduled castes or for the`
  line `scheduled tribes; and]`
  line
  line `(c) the adjustments in the boundaries and description of the extent of the parliamentary`
  line `constituencies in the State that may be necessary or expedient.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) In determining the matters referred to in clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (2), the Election`
  line `Commission shall have regard to the following provisions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) all the constituencies shall be single-member constituencies;`
  line
  line `(b) all the constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas and in`
  line `delimiting them regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication and public convenience; and`
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved either for the scheduled castes or for the scheduled`
  line `tribes shall, as far as practicable, be located in the areas in which the population of the scheduled`
  line `castes or, as the case may be, of the scheduled tribes is most concentrated, but in regard to scheduled`
  line `castes, care should be taken to distribute the reserved seats in different areas of the State.]`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of assisting the Election Commission in the performance of its functions under`
  line `sub-section (2), the Commission shall associate with itself such five persons as the Central Government`
  line `shall by order specify, being persons who are members either of the Legislative Assembly of the State or`
  line `of the House of the People representing the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the said associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of`
  line `the Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals in regard to matters mentioned in sub-section (2) in the Official Gazette`
  line `of the State together with a notice specifying the date on or after which the proposals will be further`
  line `considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line `specified, and for the purpose of such consideration, hold one or more public sittings at such place or`
  line `places as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(c) make an order revising to such extent as may be necessary or expedient the Schedules to the`
  line `Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1956, in so far as they relate to`
  line `the State; and`
  line
  line `(d) send authenticated copies of the order to the Central Government and to the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) As soon as may be after the said order is received by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, it shall be laid before the House of the People or, as the case may be, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the State.`
  line
  line `(7) An order made by the Election Commission under this section shall have the full force of law and`
  line `shall not be called in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 1961, s. 6, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 9-3-1961).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-3-1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (43609)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Amendment of article 168 of the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43609&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in article 168 of`
  line `the Constitution, in sub-clause (a) of clause (1), the word "Bombay" shall be omitted, and after the word`
  line `"Madras", the word "Maharashtra" shall be inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (43610)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Legislative Council of Maharashtra.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43610&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, there shall be 78 seats in the`
  line `Legislative Council of Maharashtra, and in the Third Schedule to the Representation of the People Act,`
  line `1950 (43 of 1950),—`
  line
  line `(a) the entry No. 3 relating to Bombay shall be omitted and the existing entries 4 and 5 shall be`
  line `renumbered as entries 3 and 4 respectively;`
  line
  line `(b) after the entry relating to Madras, the following entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"5. Maharashtra.. 78 22 7 7 30 12".`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (43611)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Council constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43611&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the Delimitation of Council Constituencies`
  line `(Bombay) Order, 1951 shall stand amended as directed in the Fifth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (43612)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Provision as to certain sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43612&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed day—`
  line
  line `(a) the sitting members of the Legislative Council of Bombay specified in the Sixth Schedule`
  line `shall cease to be members of that Council; and`
  line
  line `(b) all other sitting members of that Council shall become members of the Legislative Council of`
  line `Maharashtra and any such sitting member representing a council constituency the extent of which is`
  line `altered by virtue of the provisions of section 22 shall be deemed to have been elected to the`
  line `Legislative Council of Maharashtra by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the members referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall remain`
  line unaltered.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (43613)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Special provision as to biennial elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43613&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 16 of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951), no notification under that section`
  line `shall be published before the appointed day for holding biennial elections to fill the seats of members of`
  line `the Legislative Council of Bombay, retiring on the expiration of their term of office on the 24th day`
  line `of April, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the members of the said Council elected to fill the vacancies at the said`
  line `biennial elections shall expire on the 24th day of April, 1966.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (43614)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Chairman and Deputy Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43614&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The person who immediately before the appointed day`
  line `is the Deputy Chairman of the Legislative Council of Bombay shall be the Deputy Chairman of the`
  line `Legislative Council of Maharashtra.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the completion of the biennial elections referred to in section 24, the`
  line `Legislative Council of Maharashtra shall choose one of its members to be the Chairman thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (43615)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Amendment of the Scheduled Castes Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43615&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Seventh Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (43616)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Amendment of the Scheduled Tribes Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43616&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Eighth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (43617)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `High Court for Gujarat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43617&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, there shall be a separate High Court`
  line `for the State of Gujarat (hereinafter referred to as "the High Court of Gujarat") and the High Court of`
  line `Bombay shall become the High Court for the State of Maharashtra (hereinafter referred to as the High`
  line `Court at Bombay).`
  line
  line `(2) The principal seat of the High Court of Gujarat shall be at such place as the President may, by`
  line `notified order, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Judges and division courts of the High`
  line `Court of Gujarat may sit at such other place or places in the State of Gujarat other than its principal seat`
  line `as the Chief Justice may, with the approval of the Governor of Gujarat, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (43618)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Judges of Gujarat High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43618&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such of the Judges of the High Court of Bombay holding`
  line `office immediately before the appointed day as may be determined by the President shall on that day`
  line `cease to be Judges of the High Court at Bombay and become Judges of the High Court of Gujarat.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons who by virtue of sub-section (1) become Judges of the High Court of Gujarat shall,`
  line `except in the case where any such person is appointed to be the Chief Justice of that High Court, rank in`
  line `that Court according to the priority of their respective appointments as Judges of the High Court of`
  line Bombay.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (43619)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Jurisdiction of Gujarat High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43619&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The High Court of Gujarat shall have, in respect of any`
  line `part of the territories included in the State of Gujarat, all such jurisdiction, powers and authority as, under`
  line `the law in force immediately before the appointed day, are exercisable in respect of that part of the said`
  line `territories by the High Court of Bombay.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (43687)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43687&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `[Power to enrol advocates, etc.]—Rep. by the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), s. 50 and the`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 4-1-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (43688)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Practice and procedure in Gujarat High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43688&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the law`
  line `in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court of`
  line `Bombay shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of Gujarat, and`
  line `accordingly, the High Court of Gujarat shall have all such powers to make rules and orders with respect to`
  line `practice and procedure as are immediately before the appointed day exercisable by the High Court of`
  line `Bombay:`
  line
  line `Provided that any rules or orders which are in force immediately before the appointed day with`
  line `respect to practice and procedure in the High Court of Bombay shall, until varied or revoked by rules or`
  line `orders made by the High Court of Gujarat, apply with the necessary modifications in relation to practice`
  line `and procedure in the High Court of Gujarat as if made by that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (43621)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Custody of seal of Gujarat High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43621&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Bombay shall, with the necessary`
  line `modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (43622)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43622&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of`
  line `Bombay shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other`
  line `processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (43623)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43623&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day relating to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Bombay and with`
  line `respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary modifications,`
  line `apply in relation to the High Court of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (43624)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43624&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Bombay and the Judges`
  line `and division courts thereof shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of`
  line Gujarat.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (43625)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Transfer of proceeding from Bombay High Court to Gujarat High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43625&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as`
  line `hereinafter provided, the High Court at Bombay shall, as from the appointed day, have no jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of the transferred territory.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court of Bombay immediately before the appointed day as`
  line `are certified, whether before or after that day, by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the`
  line `place of accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard`
  line `and decided by the High Court of Gujarat shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred`
  line `to the High Court of Gujarat.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section or in section 30, but`
  line `save as hereinafter provided, the High Court at Bombay shall have, and the High Court of Gujarat shall`
  line `not have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the`
  line `Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where any such proceedings seek any relief`
  line `in respect of any order passed by the High Court of Bombay before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if after any such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court at Bombay, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Gujarat, he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court of Bombay—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day, in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Gujarat by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Bombay retains jurisdiction by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall for all purposes have effect, not only as an order of the High Court at Bombay, but also as an order`
  line `made by the High Court of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (43626)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to Gujarat High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43626&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Any person,`
  line `who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise, or an attorney entitled to`
  line `act, in the High Court of Bombay and was authorised to appear or to act in any proceedings transferred`
  line `from that High Court to the High Court of Gujarat under section 37, shall have the right to appear or to`
  line `act, as the case may be, in the High Court of Gujarat in relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (43627)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43627&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 37—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof, and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (43628)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43628&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the High Court of Gujarat of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be made`
  line `on or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority having`
  line `power to make such provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (43629)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Permanent Bench of Bombay High Court at Nagpur.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43629&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `section 51 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956), such Judges of the High Court at Bombay,`
  line `being not less than three in number, as the Chief Justice may from time to time nominate, shall sit at`
  line `Nagpur in order to exercise the jurisdiction and power for the time being vested in that High Court in`
  line `respect of cases arising in the districts of Buldana, Akola, Amravati, Yeotmal, Wardha, Nagpur,`
  line `Bhandara, Chanda and Rajura:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Justice may, in his discretion, order that any case arising in any such district`
  line `shall be heard at Bombay.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (43630)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Authorisation of expenditure of Gujarat State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43630&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Governor of Bombay may, at any time`
  line `before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Gujarat`
  line `as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the appointed day pending`
  line `the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of the State of Gujarat:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Gujarat may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Gujarat for any period not`
  line `extending beyond the said period of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (43631)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Reports relating to accounts of Bombay State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43631&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports of the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 relating to the accounts of the State of`
  line `Bombay in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the Governor of each of`
  line `the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislature of the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may by order—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of Bombay on any service in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial year 1960-61 or in respect of any`
  line `earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service and for that year as disclosed in`
  line `the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (43632)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Allowances and privileges of Governor of Gujarat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43632&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and privileges of the`
  line `Governor of Gujarat shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under clause (3) of`
  line `article 158, be such as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (43633)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43633&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Section 3 of the Union Duties of Excise (Distribution)`
  line `Act, 1957 (55 of 1957), sections 3 and 5 of the Estate Duty and Tax on Railway Passenger Fares`
  line `(Distribution) Act, 1957 (57 of 1957), section 4 of, and the Second Schedule to, the Additional Duties of`
  line `Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), and paragraph 3 of the Constitution`
  line `(Distribution of Revenues) No. 2 Order, 1957, shall have effect subject to such modifications as are`
  line `specified in the Ninth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The total amount payable to the State of Maharashtra under the enactments and Order referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) in respect of the part of the financial year 1960-61 beginning with the appointed`
  line `day and in respect of the financial year 1961-62 shall be reduced by a sum of 602 lakhs of rupees and`
  line `614 lakhs of rupees, respectively and the total amount payable to the State of Gujarat, under those`
  line `enactments and Order in respect of each of those periods shall be correspondingly increased.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (43634)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Application of Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43634&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Part shall apply in relation to the apportionment of`
  line `the assets and liabilities of the State of Bombay immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (43635)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Land and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43635&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles`
  line `and other goods belonging to the State of Bombay shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if within the transferred territory, pass to the State of Gujarat; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, remain the property of the State of Maharashtra:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government is of opinion that any goods or class of goods should be`
  line `distributed otherwise than according to the situation of the goods, the Central Government may issue such`
  line `directions as it thinks fit for a just and equitable distribution of the goods and the goods shall remain the`
  line `property of the State of Maharashtra or, as the case may be, pass to the State of Gujarat, accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such stores of the State of Bombay as are referred to in the Tenth Schedule shall be divided`
  line `between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in the manner specified therein.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every kind and any rights in`
  line `or over such property, and the expression "goods" does not include coins, bank notes and currency notes.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (43636)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Treasury and bank balances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43636&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The total of the cash balances in all treasuries of the State of`
  line `Bombay and the credit balances of that State with the Reserve Bank of India, the State Bank of India and`
  line `the State Bank of Saurashtra immediately before the appointed day shall be divided between the States of`
  line `Maharashtra and Gujarat according to the population ratio:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of such division, there shall be no transfer of cash balances from any`
  line `treasury to any other treasury and the apportionment shall be effected by adjusting the credit balances of`
  line `the two States in the books of the Reserve Bank of India on the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the State of Gujarat has no account on the appointed day with the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India, the adjustment shall be made in such manner as the Central Government may, by order,`
  line direct.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (43637)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43637&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover arrears of any tax or duty on property, including arrears`
  line `of land revenue, shall belong to the State in which the property is situated, and the right to recover arrears`
  line `of any other tax or duty shall belong to the State in whose territories the place of assessment of that tax or`
  line `duty is included on the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that any sum recovered after the appointed day in respect of any arrears of tax accruing`
  line `during the period between the 1st day of January, 1960, and the 30th day of April, 1960 (both`
  line `days inclusive) under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956), or the Bombay Sales Tax`
  line `Act, 1959 (Bom. Act LI of 1959), shall, after deducting the cost of collection thereof, be divided between`
  line `the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat according to the population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (43638)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Right to recover loans and advances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43638&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right of the State of Bombay to recover any`
  line `loans or advances made before the appointed day to any local body, society, agriculturist or other person`
  line `in an area within that State shall belong to the State in which that area is included on that day.`
  line
  line `(2) The right of the State of Bombay to recover any loans or advances made before the appointed day`
  line `to any person or institution outside that State shall belong to the State of Maharashtra:`
  line
  line `Provided that any sum recovered in respect of any such loan or advance shall be divided between the`
  line `States of Maharashtra and Gujarat according to the population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (43639)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Credits in certain funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43639&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Out of the investments of the State of Bombay made before the`
  line `appointed day in the cash balance investment account of the State, such securities of the value of ten`
  line `crores of rupees, as the Central Government may by order specify, shall pass to the State of Gujarat in`
  line `connection with the construction of a capital for that State; and the remaining investments in the said`
  line `account shall be divided between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat according to the population ratio.`
  line
  line `(2) The investments of the State of Bombay immediately before the appointed day in the State`
  line `Famine Relief Fund, the State Road Fund, the Fund for Development Schemes, the Insurance Fund, the`
  line `Bombay State Milk Fund, the Securities Adjustment Reserve Fund and any other general fund and the`
  line `sums at the credit of that State in the Central Road Fund shall be divided between the States of`
  line `Maharashtra and Gujarat according to the population ratio.`
  line
  line `(3) The investments of the State of Bombay immediately before the appointed day in the Dangs`
  line `District Reserve Fund, the Port Reserve Fund, the Port Development Fund and the Anand Institute Fund`
  line `shall pass to the State of Gujarat and the investments in any other special fund the objects of which are`
  line `confined to a local area shall belong to the State in which that area is included on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The investments of the State of Bombay immediately before the appointed day in any private`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking, in so far as such investments have not been made or are deemed not`
  line `to have been made from the cash balance investment account, shall pass to the State in which the`
  line `principal seat of business of the undertaking is located.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any body corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act for the`
  line `State of Bombay or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, become an inter-State body`
  line `corporate, the investments in, or loans or advances to, any such body corporate by the State of Bombay`
  line `made before the appointed day shall, save as otherwise expressly provided by or under this Act, be`
  line `divided between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in the same proportion in which the assets of the`
  line `body corporate are divided under the provisions of Part VII.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (43640)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Special Revenue Reserve Fund in Gujarat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43640&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Out of the investments in the cash balance`
  line `investment account which remain with the State of Maharashtra after giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `section 51, such securities of the value of 1,420 lakhs of rupees as the Central Government may by order`
  line `specify shall stand transferred to the State of Gujarat.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be constituted in the State of Gujarat a Fund to be called the Special Revenue Reserve`
  line `Fund consisting of the securities transferred to that State under sub-section (1) and such other securities`
  line `belonging to the State of Gujarat of the value of 1,419 lakhs of rupees as the Central Government may by`
  line `order specify.`
  line
  line `(3) From and out of the fund constituted under sub-section (2), there shall be transferred as receipts in`
  line `the revenue account of the State of Gujarat in each of the financial years specified in column 1 of the`
  line `following Table a sum set out against that year in column 2 thereof, and in the financial year 1969-70, the`
  line `balance, if any, remaining in that fund:—`
  line
  line TABLE
  line
  line `Financial year Amount in lakhs of rupees.`
  line
  line `(1) (2)`
  line
  line `1962-63 612`
  line
  line `1963-64 585`
  line
  line `1964-65 561`
  line
  line `1965-66 526`
  line
  line `1966-67 433`
  line
  line `1967-68 340`
  line
  line `1968-69 209`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (43641)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Assets and liabilities of State undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43641&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assets and liabilities relating to any`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking of the State of Bombay shall pass to the State in which the`
  line `undertaking is located.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a depreciation reserve fund is maintained by the State of Bombay for any such commercial`
  line `or industrial undertaking, the securities held in respect of investments made from that fund shall pass to`
  line `the State in which the undertaking is located.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (43642)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Public debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43642&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The public debt of the State of Bombay attributable to loans raised by the issue`
  line `of Government securities and outstanding with the public immediately before the appointed day shall, as`
  line `from that day, be the debt of the State of Maharashtra:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) the State of Gujarat shall be liable to pay to the State of Maharashtra its share of the sums due`
  line `from time to time for the servicing and repayment of the debt; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of determining the said share, the debt shall be deemed to be divided between`
  line `the States of Maharashtra, and Gujarat as if it were a debt referred to in sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3), as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The public debt of the State of Bombay attributable to loans taken from the Central Government,`
  line `the National Co-operative Development and Warehousing Board or the Khadi and Village Industries`
  line `Commission or from any other source for the express purpose of re-lending the same to a specific`
  line `institution and outstanding immediately before the appointed day shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if re-lent to any local body, body corporate or other institution in any local area, be the debt of`
  line `the State in which the local area is included on the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(b) if re-lent to the Bombay State Electricity Board, the Bombay State Road Transport`
  line `Corporation, or the Bombay Housing Board or any other institution which becomes an inter-State`
  line `institution on the appointed day, be divided between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in the`
  line `same proportion in which the assets of such body corporate or institution are divided under the`
  line `provisions of Part VII.`
  line
  line `(3) The remaining public debt of the State of Bombay attributable to loans taken from the Central`
  line `Government, the Reserve Bank of India or any other body corporate and outstanding immediately before`
  line `the appointed day shall be divided between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in proportion to the`
  line `total expenditure on all capital works and other capital outlays incurred or deemed to have been incurred`
  line `up to the appointed day in the territories included respectively in each of those States:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of such division, only the expenditure on assets for which capital`
  line `accounts have been kept shall be taken into account.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Where any expenditure on capital works or other capital outlays cannot be allocated`
  line `between the territories included in the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat, such expenditure shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section, be deemed to have been incurred in those territories according to the`
  line `population ratio.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a sinking fund or a depreciation fund is maintained by the State of Bombay for repayment`
  line `of any loan raised by it, the securities held in respect of investments made from that fund shall be divided`
  line `between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in the same proportion in which the total public debt is`
  line `divided between the two States under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, the fund in the public account of the State of`
  line `Bombay known as the Debt Redemption and Avoidance Fund shall be deemed to be a sinking fund.`
  line
  line `(5) The share of the State of Gujarat in the liability on account of public debt apportioned under`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be reduced by 1,419 lakhs of rupees and the share of the State of Maharashtra in`
  line `such liability shall be correspondingly increased.`
  line
  line `(6) In this section, the expression "Government security" means a security created and issued by a`
  line `State Government for the purpose of raising a public loan and having any of the forms specified in, or`
  line `prescribed under clause (2) of section 2 of the Public Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (43643)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Floating Debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43643&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability of the State of Bombay in respect of any floating debt of a`
  line `Merged State shall be the liability of the State in whose territories the area of the Merged State is included`
  line `on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The liability of the State of Bombay in respect of any other floating loan to provide short-term`
  line `finance to any commercial undertaking shall be the liability of the State in whose territories the`
  line `undertaking is located.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (43644)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43644&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the State of Bombay to refund any tax or`
  line `duty on property, including land revenue, collected in excess shall be the liability of the State in which the`
  line `property is situated, and the liability of the State of Bombay to refund any other tax or duty collected in`
  line `excess shall be the liability of the State in whose territories the place of assessment of that tax or duty is`
  line `included:`
  line
  line `Provided that the liability to refund any amount after the appointed day on account of any excess`
  line `collected in respect of any tax accruing during the period between the 1st day of January, 1960, and the`
  line `30th day of April, 1960 (both days inclusive) under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956) or the`
  line `Bombay Sales Tax Act, 1959 (Bom. Act LI of 1959), shall be shared between the two States of`
  line `Maharashtra and Gujarat according to the population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (43645)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Deposits, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43645&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability of the State of Bombay in respect of any civil deposit or local`
  line `fund deposit shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of the State in whose area the deposit has`
  line `been made.`
  line
  line `(2) The liability of the State of Bombay in respect of any charitable or other endowment shall, as`
  line `from the appointed day, be the liability of the State in whose area the institution entitled to the benefit of`
  line `the endowment is located or of the State to which the objects of the endowment, under the terms thereof,`
  line `are confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (43646)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43646&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the State of Bombay in respect of the provident fund account`
  line `of a Government servant in service on the appointed day shall, as from that day, be the liability of the`
  line `State to which that Government servant is permanently allotted.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (43647)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title Pensions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43647&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the State of Bombay in respect of pensions shall pass to, or be`
  line `apportioned between, the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in accordance with the provisions contained`
  line `in the Eleventh Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (43648)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43648&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the appointed day, the State of Bombay has made any contract in`
  line `the exercise of its executive power for any purposes of the State, that contract shall be deemed to have`
  line `been made in the exercise of the executive power,—`
  line
  line `(a) if such purposes are, as from that day, exclusively purposes of either the State of Maharashtra`
  line `or the State of Gujarat, of that State; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, of the State of Maharashtra;`
  line
  line `and all rights and liabilities which have accrued, or may accrue, under any such contract shall, to the`
  line `extent to which they would have been rights or liabilities of the State of Bombay, be rights or liabilities of`
  line `the State of Maharashtra or the State of Gujarat, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any such case as is referred to in clause (b), the initial allocation of rights and`
  line `liabilities made by this sub-section shall be subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon`
  line `between the State of Maharashtra and the State of Gujarat or, in default of such agreement, as the Central`
  line `Government may by order direct.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations; and bank`
  line `balances and securities shall, notwithstanding that they partake of the nature of contractual rights, be dealt`
  line `with under those provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (43649)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43649&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `State of Bombay is subject to any liability in respect of any actionable wrong other than breach of`
  line `contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the cause of action arose wholly within the territories which, as from that day, are the`
  line `territories of the State of Maharashtra or the State of Gujarat, be a liability of that State; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be initially a liability of the State of Maharashtra, but subject to such`
  line `financial adjustment as may be agreed upon between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat or, in`
  line `default of such agreement, as the Central Government may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (43650)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Liability as guarantor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43650&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the State of Bombay is`
  line `liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered cooperative society or other person, that`
  line `liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the area of operations of such society or person is limited to the territories which, as from`
  line `that day, are the territories of the State of Maharashtra or of the State of Gujarat, be a liability of that`
  line `State; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be initially a liability of the State of Maharashtra, subject to such financial`
  line `adjustment as may be agreed upon between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat or, in default of`
  line `such agreement, as the Central Government may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (43651)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Items in suspense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43651&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (43652)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Residuary provision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43652&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The benefit or burden of any asset or liability of the State of Bombay not`
  line `dealt with in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall pass to the State of Maharashtra in the first`
  line `instance, subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon between the States of Maharashtra`
  line `and Gujarat before the 1st day of April, 1961 or, in default of such agreement, as the Central Government`
  line `may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (43653)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43653&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Where the States of Maharashtra and`
  line `Gujarat agree that the benefit or burden of any particular asset or liability should be apportioned between`
  line `them in a manner other than that provided for in the foregoing provisions of this Part, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained therein, the benefit or burden of that asset or liability shall be`
  line `apportioned in the manner agreed upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (43654)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43654&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line Where,
  line `by virtue of any of the provisions of this Part, any of the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat becomes`
  line `entitled to any property or obtains any benefits or becomes subject to any liability, and the Central`
  line `Government, on a reference made within a period of three years from the appointed day by either of the`
  line `States, is of opinion that it is just and equitable that that property or those benefits should be transferred`
  line `to, or shared with, the other State or that a contribution towards that liability should be made by the other`
  line `State, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in such manner between the two States, or the other`
  line `State shall make to the State subject to the liability such contribution in respect thereof, as the Central`
  line `Government may, after consultation with the two State Governments, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (43655)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Certain expenditure to be charged on Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43655&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `All sums payable either by the`
  line `State of Maharashtra or by the State of Gujarat to the other State or by the Central Government to either`
  line `of those States, by virtue of the provisions of this Act, shall be charged on the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `State by which such sums are payable or, as the case may be, the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (43656)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Provisions as to Bombay State Electricity Board and State Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43656&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following bodies corporate constituted for the State of Bombay, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the State Electricity Board constituted under the Electricity Supply Act, 1948 (54 of 1948);`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the State Warehousing Corporation established under the Agricultural Produce (Development`
  line `and Warehousing) Corporations Act, 1956 (28 of 1956),`
  line
  line `shall, as from the appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which they were`
  line `functioning immediately before that day, subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as`
  line `may, from time to time, be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the Board or`
  line `the Corporation shall include a direction that the Act under which the Board or the Corporation was`
  line `constituted shall, in its application to that Board or Corporation, have effect subject to such exceptions`
  line `and modifications as the Central Government thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1) shall cease to function as from, and`
  line `shall be deemed to be dissolved on, the 1st day of October, 1960, or such earlier date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, appoint; and upon such dissolution, its assets, rights and liabilities shall be`
  line `apportioned between the State of Maharashtra and the State of Gujarat in such manner as may be agreed`
  line `upon between them within one year of the dissolution of the Board or the Corporation, as the case may`
  line `be, or if no agreement is reached, in such manner as the Central Government may by order determine.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of the State of Maharashtra or, as the case may be, the Government of the State of Gujarat`
  line `from constituting, at any time on or after the appointed day, a State Electricity Board or a State`
  line `Warehousing Corporation for that State under the provisions of the Act relating to such Board or`
  line `Corporation; and if such a Board or Corporation is so constituted in either of the States before the`
  line `dissolution of the Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) provision may be made by order of the Central Government enabling the new Board or the`
  line `new Corporation to take over from the existing Board or Corporation all or any of its undertakings,`
  line `assets, rights and liabilities in that State, and`
  line
  line `(b) upon the dissolution of the existing Board or Corporation, any assets, rights and liabilities`
  line `which would otherwise have passed to that State by or under the provisions of sub-section (3) shall`
  line `pass to the new Board or the new Corporation instead of to that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (43686)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Continuance of arrangements in regard to generation and supply of electric power and supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43686&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Central Government that the arrangement in regard to the`
  line `generation or supply of electric power or the supply of water for any area or in regard to the execution of`
  line `any project for such generation or supply has been or is likely to be modified to the disadvantage of that`
  line `area by reason of the fact that it is, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, outside the State in which the`
  line `power stations and other installations for the generation and supply of such power, or the catchment area,`
  line `reservoirs and other works for the supply of water, as the case may be, are located, the Central`
  line `Government may give such directions as it deems proper to the State Government or other authority`
  line `concerned for the maintenance, so far as practicable, of the previous arrangement.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (43658)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Provisions as to Bombay State Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43658&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bombay State Financial`
  line `Corporation established under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951) shall, as from the`
  line `appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which it was functioning immediately`
  line `before that day, subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as may, from time to time,`
  line `be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the`
  line `Corporation shall include a direction that the said Act, in its application to the Corporation, shall have`
  line `effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) A general meeting of the Corporation shall be convened, in accordance with the rules to be made`
  line `in this behalf by the Central Government, by the Board thereof before the 31st day of July, 1960, or`
  line `within such further time as the Central Government may allow, for the consideration of a scheme for the`
  line `reconstitution or reorganisation or dissolution, as the case may be, of the Corporation, including proposals`
  line `regarding the formation of new corporations, and the transfer thereto of the assets, rights and liabilities`
  line `of the existing Corporation, and if such a scheme is approved at the general meeting by a resolution`
  line `passed by a majority of the shareholders present and voting, the scheme shall be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government for its sanction.`
  line
  line `(4) If the scheme is sanctioned by the Central Government either without modifications or with`
  line `modifications which are approved at a general meeting, the Central Government shall certify the scheme,`
  line `and upon such certification, the scheme shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, be binding on the corporations affected by the scheme as well as the`
  line `shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) If the scheme is not so approved or sanctioned, the Central Government may refer the scheme to`
  line `such Judge of the High Court at Bombay as may be nominated in this behalf by the Chief Justice thereof,`
  line `and the decision of the Judge in regard to the scheme shall be final and shall be binding on the`
  line `corporations affected by the scheme as well as the shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing`
  line `the Government of the State of Gujarat from constituting, at any time on or after the appointed day, a`
  line `State Financial Corporation for that State under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (43659)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Amendment of Act 64 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43659&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `In the Road Transport Corporations Act, 1950,—`
  line
  line `(1) in section 47A,—`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(i) for the words, letters and figures, "the whole or any part of a State in respect of which`
  line `a Corporation was, immediately before the 1st day of November, 1956", the words "or any`
  line `other enactment relating to reorganisation of States, the whole or any part of a State in respect`
  line `of which a Corporation was, immediately before the day on which the reorganisation takes`
  line `place", shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the Explanation, for clause (i), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(i) in relation to the Bombay State Road Transport Corporation, shall mean`
  line `the Government of the State of Maharashtra or of Gujarat as formed under the`
  line `Bombay Reorganisation Act, 1960;";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), in clause (f), after "the words and figures the States Reorganisation Act,`
  line `1956", the words "or any other enactment relating to reorganisation of States" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(2) after section 47A, the following section shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"48. Transitional provision relating to Bombay State Road Transport`
  line `Corporation.—Notwithstanding anything contained in section 47A, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Government of the State of Bombay to frame a scheme under sub-section (1) thereof and forward`
  line `the same to the Central Government before the 1st day of May, 1960, and in such a case, the`
  line `power conferred on the Central Government to make an order under sub-section (2) thereof may`
  line `be exercised before that day but no order so made shall take effect till that day.".`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (43660)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Special provision for Bar Council of Gujarat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43660&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the Indian Bar Councils`
  line `Act, 1926 (38 of 1926),—`
  line
  line `(a) in section 4,—`
  line
  line `(i) to sub-section (2), the following Explanation shall be added, namely:—`
  line
  line `"Explanation.—For the purpose of election to the Bar Council for the High Court of`
  line `Gujarat, the period of ten years aforesaid shall be computed after taking into account the`
  line `period for which the person concerned was entitled as of right to practise in the High Court of`
  line `Bombay or of Saurashtra or in the Judicial Commissioner's Court of Kutch before the 1st day`
  line `of May, 1960.";`
  line
  line `(ii) for the proviso to sub-section (4), the following proviso shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"Provided that the Advocates-General of West Bengal, Madras, Maharashtra and Gujarat`
  line `shall be Chairmen ex-officio, respectively, of the Bar Councils constituted for the`
  line `High Courts of those States.";`
  line
  line `(b) after section 5, the following section shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"5A. Ad hoc Bar Council for Gujarat High Court.—Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act, the Chief Justice of the High Court of Gujarat shall nominate the members of the first`
  line `Bar Council under this Act for the High Court of Gujarat and the members so nominated shall`
  line `remain in office for a period of twelve months.".`
  line
  line `(2) The assets and liabilities of the Bar Council for the High Court of Bombay shall be divided`
  line `between the Bar Councils for the High Court at Bombay and the High Court of Gujarat in such manner as`
  line `may be agreed upon, and in default of such agreement, as may be directed by the Attorney-General for`
  line India.
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (43661)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Amendment of Act 6 of 1942.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43661&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `In the Multi-unit Co-operative Societies Act, 1942, after`
  line `section 5B, the following section shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"5C. Transitional provision relating to certain multi-unit cooperative societies.—(1) Where,`
  line `in respect of any co-operative society specified in the Twelfth Schedule, which under the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 5A becomes a multi-unit co-operative society, the Board of Directors`
  line `unanimously adopts any scheme for the reconstitution, reorganisation or dissolution of the society,`
  line `including proposals for the formation of new co-operative societies and the transfer thereto of the`
  line `assets and liabilities and employees of that society and the State Government of Bombay certifies the`
  line `scheme at any time before the 1st day of May, 1960, then notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of the said section or any other law, regulation or`
  line `bye-law for the time being in force in relation to that society, the scheme so certified shall be binding`
  line `on all societies affected by the scheme, as well as the shareholders, creditors and employees of all`
  line `such societies, subject to such financial adjustments as may be directed in this behalf under`
  line `sub-section (3), but no such scheme shall be given effect to before the said day.`
  line
  line `(2) When a scheme in respect of a co-operative society is so certified, the Central Registrar shall`
  line `place the scheme at a meeting, held in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act, of`
  line `all the persons who, immediately before the date of certification of the scheme, were members of the`
  line `society and the scheme may be approved by a resolution passed by a majority of the members present and`
  line `voting at the said meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) If the scheme is not so approved or is approved with modifications, the Central Registrar may`
  line `refer the scheme to such Judge of the High Court at Bombay as may be nominated in this behalf by the`
  line `Chief Justice thereof and the Judge may direct such financial adjustments to be made among the societies`
  line `affected as he deems necessary, and the scheme shall be deemed to be approved subject to those financial`
  line adjustments.
  line
  line `(4) If in consequence of the directions given under sub-section (3), a society becomes liable to pay`
  line `any sum of money, the State within whose area the society is located shall be liable as guarantor in`
  line `respect of the payment of such money.".`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (43662)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `General provision as to statutory corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43662&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided by`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Part, where any body corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act`
  line `or Provincial Act for the State of Bombay or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of Part II,`
  line `become an inter-State body corporate, then, the body corporate shall, as from the appointed day, continue`
  line `to function and operate in those areas in respect of which it was functioning and operating immediately`
  line `before that day, subject to such directions as may from time to time be issued by the Central Government,`
  line `until other provision is made by law in respect of the said body corporate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of any such`
  line `body corporate shall include a direction that any law by which the said body corporate is governed shall,`
  line `in its application to that body corporate, have effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may`
  line `be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (43663)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Amendment of Act 38 of 1957.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43663&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `In the Inter-State Corporations Act, 1957, in the preamble, in`
  line `section 2, in clause (f) of sub-section (2) of section 4 and in section 5, after the words and figures "the`
  line `States Reorganisation Act, 1956", wherever they occur, the words "or of any other enactment relating to`
  line `reorganisation of States" shall be inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (43664)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Temporary provisions as to continuance of certain existing road transport permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43664&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 63 of the Motor Vehicles`
  line `Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), a permit granted by the State Transport Authority of Bombay or any Regional`
  line `Transport Authority in that State shall, if such permit was, immediately before the appointed day, valid`
  line `and effective in any area in the transferred territory, be deemed to continue to be valid and effective in`
  line `that area after that day subject to the provisions of that Act as for the time being in force in that area; and`
  line `it shall not be necessary for any such permit to be countersigned by the State Transport Authority of`
  line `Gujarat or any Regional Transport Authority therein for the purpose of validating it for use in such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Governments of`
  line `Maharashtra and Gujarat, add to, amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the Authority by`
  line `which the permit was granted.`
  line
  line `(2) No tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature shall be levied after the appointed day in`
  line `respect of any transport vehicle for its operations in the State of Gujarat under any such permit, if such`
  line `vehicle was, immediately before that day, exempt from the payment of any such toll, entrance fees or`
  line `other charges for its operations in the transferred territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Governments of`
  line `Maharashtra and Gujarat, authorise the levy of any such toll, entrance fees or other charges, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (43665)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Special provision relating to retrenchment compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43665&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Where on`
  line `account of the reorganisation of the State of Bombay under this Act, any body corporate constituted under`
  line `a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act, any co-operative society registered under any law relating to`
  line `co-operative societies or any commercial or industrial undertaking of that State is reconstituted or`
  line `reorganised in any manner whatsoever or is amalgamated with any other body corporate, co-operative`
  line `society or undertaking, or is dissolved, and in consequence of such reconstitution, reorganisation,`
  line `amalgamation or dissolution, any workman employed by such body corporate or in any such co-operative`
  line `society or undertaking, is transferred to, or re-employed by any other body corporate, or in any other cooperative society or undertaking, then notwithstanding anything contained in section 25F of the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), such transfer or re-employment shall not entitle him to any`
  line `compensation under that section;`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the workman after such transfer or`
  line `re-employment are not less favourable to the workman than those applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the transfer or re-employment;`
  line
  line `(b) the employer in relation to the body corporate, the cooperative society or the undertaking`
  line `where the workman is transferred or re-employed is, by agreement or otherwise, legally liable`
  line `to pay to the workman, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation under section 25F of the`
  line `Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), on the basis that his service has been continuous and has`
  line `not been interrupted by the transfer or re-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (43666)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Special provision as to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43666&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Where the assets, rights and liabilities of any body`
  line `corporate carrying on any business are, under the provisions of this Part, transferred to any other`
  line `bodies corporate which after the transfer carry on the same business, the losses of profits or gains`
  line `sustained by the body corporate first mentioned which, but for such transfer, would have been allowed to`
  line `be carried forward and set off in accordance with the provisions of section 24 of the Indian Income-tax`
  line `Act, 1922 (11 of 1922), shall be apportioned amongst the transferee bodies corporate in accordance with`
  line `the rules to be made by the Central Government in this behalf and, upon such apportionment, the share of`
  line `loss allotted to each transferee body corporate shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 24 of the said Act, as if the transferee body corporate had itself sustained such loss in a business`
  line `carried on by it in the years in which these losses were sustained.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (43667)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Continuance of facilities in certain State institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43667&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government of the State of`
  line `Maharashtra or, as the case may be, the Government of the State of Gujarat shall, in respect of the`
  line `institutions specified in the Thirteenth Schedule located in that State, continue to provide facilities to the`
  line `people of the other State which shall not, in any respect, be less favourable to such people than what were`
  line `being provided to them before the appointed day, for such period and upon such terms and conditions as`
  line `may be agreed upon between the two State Governments before the 1st day of October, 1960, or, if no`
  line `agreement is reached by the said date, as may be fixed by order of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, at any time before the 1st day of October, 1960, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify in the Thirteenth Schedule any other institution existing on the appointed day`
  line `in the State of Maharashtra or of Gujarat, and on the issue of such notification, the Schedule shall be`
  line `deemed to be amended by the inclusion of the said institution therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (43668)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Provisions relating to All-India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43668&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, the expression "State cadre"—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the`
  line `Indian Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954, and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Police`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954.`
  line
  line `(2) In place of the cadres of the Indian Administrative Service and the Indian Police Service existing`
  line `in the State of Bombay immediately before the appointed day, there shall, as from that day, be two`
  line `separate cadres, one for the State of Maharashtra, and the other for the State of Gujarat, in respect of each`
  line `of these services.`
  line
  line `(3) The initial strength and composition of each of the State cadres shall be such as the`
  line `Central Government may by order determine before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) The members of each of the said services borne on those cadres for the State of Bombay`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall be allocated to the State cadres of the same service for each of`
  line `the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat in such manner and with effect from such date or dates as the`
  line `Central Government may, by order, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation, after the appointed day, of the`
  line `All-India Services Act, 1951 (61 of 1951), or the rules made thereunder in relation to the State cadres of`
  line `the said services constituted under sub-section (2) and in relation to the members of those services borne`
  line `on the said cadres.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (43669)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Provisions relating to other services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43669&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, is serving in connection with the affairs of the State of Bombay shall, as from that day, provisionally`
  line `continue to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of Maharashtra, unless he is required, by`
  line `general or special order of the Central Government, to serve provisionally in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the State of Gujarat.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Central Government shall, by general or special`
  line `order, determine the State to which every person provisionally allotted to the State of Maharashtra or`
  line `Gujarat, shall be finally allotted for service and the date with effect from which such allotment shall take`
  line `effect or be deemed to have taken effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is finally allotted under the provisions of sub-section (2) to the State of`
  line `Maharashtra or Gujarat shall, if he is not already serving therein, be made available for serving in that`
  line `State from such date as may be agreed upon between the two State Governments or, in default of such`
  line `agreement, as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may by order establish one or more Advisory Committees for the`
  line `purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the division and integration of the services among the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `section and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
  line
  line `(5) The foregoing provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to any person to whom the`
  line `provisions of section 80 apply.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect, after the appointed day, the operation of the`
  line `provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution in relation to the determination of the conditions`
  line `of service of persons serving in connection with the affairs of the State of Maharashtra or Gujarat:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day to the case of`
  line `any person provisionally or finally allotted to the State of Maharashtra or Gujarat under this section shall`
  line `not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (43670)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43670&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Every person who, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the State of Bombay in any area which on that day falls within the State of Maharashtra or Gujarat`
  line `shall continue to hold the same post or office in that State and shall be deemed, as from that day, to have`
  line `been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or other appropriate authority in, that`
  line `State:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority, after the`
  line `appointed day, from passing, in relation to such person, any order affecting his continuance in such post`
  line `or office.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (43671)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43671&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the State Governments of Maharashtra and Gujarat as may appear to it to be necessary for`
  line `the purpose of giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and the State Government shall`
  line `comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (43672)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Provisions as to Bombay Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43672&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Service Commission for`
  line `the State of Bombay shall, as from the appointed day, become the Public Service Commission for the`
  line `State of Maharashtra.`
  line
  line `(2) The report of the Bombay Public Service Commission as to the work done by the Commission in`
  line `respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be presented under clause (2) of article 323 to the`
  line `Governors of Maharashtra and Gujarat, and the Governor of Maharashtra shall, on receipt of such report,`
  line `cause a copy thereof together with a memorandum explaining, as far as possible, as respects the cases, if`
  line `any, where the advice of the Commission was not accepted, the reasons for such non-acceptance to be`
  line `laid before the Legislature of the State of Maharashtra and it shall not be necessary to cause such report or`
  line `any such memorandum to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (43673)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Amendment of article 371 of the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43673&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in article 371 of`
  line `the Constitution, in clause (2)—`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "the State of Bombay", the words "the State of Maharashtra or Gujarat" shall be`
  line `substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "the rest of Maharashtra", the words "and the rest of Maharashtra or, as the case`
  line `may be," shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (43674)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43674&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `In section 15 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956—`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (d), for the words "Bombay and Mysore", the words "Gujarat and Maharashtra" shall`
  line `be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (e), for the words "Madras and Kerala", the words "Madras, Mysore and Kerala"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (43675)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Territorial extent of law’s.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43675&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part II shall not be deemed to have effected any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Bombay shall, until otherwise provided`
  line `by a competent Legislature or other competent authority, be construed as meaning the territories within`
  line `that State immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (43676)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43676&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of`
  line `Maharashtra or Gujarat of any law made before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may,`
  line `before the expiration of one year from that day, by order, make such adaptations and modifications of the`
  line `law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every`
  line `such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and modifications so made until altered, repealed or`
  line `amended by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression appropriate Government means as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central Government, and as respects any other law,`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (43677)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43677&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 88 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority, required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application`
  line `in relation to the State of Maharashtra or Gujarat, construe the law in such manner, without affecting the`
  line `substance, as may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (43678)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43678&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `The Government of the`
  line `State of Gujarat, as respects the transferred territory may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `the authority, officer or person who, on or after the appointed day, shall be competent to exercise such`
  line `functions exercisable under any law in force on that day as may be mentioned in that notification and`
  line `such law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (43679)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43679&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Where immediately before the appointed day, the State of Bombay is a`
  line `party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities subject to apportionment`
  line `between the States of Maharashtra and Gujarat under this Act, the State of Maharashtra or Gujarat which`
  line `succeeds to, or acquires a share in, that property or those rights or liabilities by virtue of any provision of`
  line `this Act shall be deemed to be substituted for the State of Bombay as a party to those proceedings, and the`
  line `proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (43680)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43680&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within the State of Maharashtra shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to the`
  line `transferred territory stand transferred to the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in the State`
  line `of Gujarat.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court at Bombay and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) in this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in the State of Gujarat means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have lain if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority, or officer in that State, as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State, or before the appointed day`
  line `by the Government of Bombay, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (43681)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43681&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the State of`
  line `Bombay shall, for a period of one year from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those courts,`
  line `notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts has`
  line `been transferred to the State of Gujarat.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (43684)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43684&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (43685)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43685&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to him`
  line `to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulties.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (43683)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436&sectionId=43683&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00011_196011_1517807319436
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so, however, that any such modifications or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
